{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886486563,"sessionID":"ses_284eae57bffeVf5e1aq0wThMJ0","part":{"id":"prt_d7b154926001PsbI19o8X3kL9L","messageID":"msg_d7b1537a4001bIRWIE0DCVyW01","sessionID":"ses_284eae57bffeVf5e1aq0wThMJ0","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9072ef2d38a14bcf8e66dc3cf75ced1e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/CHANGE.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/CHANGE.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: - **AR**: AR-034\n5: - **Title**: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n6: - **Module**: .github\n7: - **Language**: YAML\n8: - **Size**: L\n9: - **Status**: Pending\n10: \n11: ## Description\n12: Create 12 GitHub Actions workflows for CI/CD pipeline automation in the AgentCube project.\n13: \n14: ## Dependencies\n15: None\n16: \n17: ## Related Changes\n18: None\n\n(End of file - total 18 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n\n## Metadata\n- **AR**: AR-034\n- **Title**: CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n- **Module**: .github\n- **Language**: YAML\n- **Size**: L\n- **Status**: Pending\n\n## Description\nCreate 12 GitHub Actions workflows for CI/CD pipeline automation in the AgentCube project.\n\n## Dependencies\nNone\n\n## Related Changes\nNone","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/CHANGE.md","time":{"start":1775886486542,"end":1775886486561}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886486566,"sessionID":"ses_284eae57bffeVf5e1aq0wThMJ0","part":{"id":"prt_d7b154be900168Lo86DDw6mQpf","messageID":"msg_d7b1537a4001bIRWIE0DCVyW01","sessionID":"ses_284eae57bffeVf5e1aq0wThMJ0","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-aabfca65360b4c138c62ba81a8a8e53a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034 Implementation Summary\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: Implemented 12 comprehensive GitHub Actions workflows for CI/CD automation in the AgentCube project, covering build verification, linting, testing, code quality checks, end-to-end testing, Python SDK validation, container image publishing, dependency updates, and workflow approval mechanisms.\n6: \n7: ## Workflows Implemented\n8: \n9: ### 1. CI Workflow (ci.yml)\n10: - **Purpose**: Docker build verification on pull requests\n11: - **Triggers**: Pull requests to `main` or `release-*` branches\n12: - **Key Features**:\n13:   - Uses Docker Buildx for multi-architecture builds\n14:   - Verifies `docker` and `buildx` versions\n15:   - Executes `make docker-build`\n16:   - Timeout: 30 minutes\n17:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n18: \n19: ### 2. Lint Workflow (lint.yml)\n20: - **Purpose**: Go code linting with path filtering\n21: - **Triggers**: Pull requests with Go-related file changes\n22: - **Path Filters**: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n23: - **Key Features**:\n24:   - Uses golangci-lint via `make lint`\n25:   - Go version 1.24\n26:   - Caching enabled for Go modules\n27:   - Concurrency control enabled\n28:   - Timeout: 15 minutes\n29: \n30: ### 3. Codegen Check Workflow (codegen-check.yml)\n31: - **Purpose**: Code generation drift detection\n32: - **Triggers**: Pull requests with API, hack, workflow, or Makefile changes\n33: - **Key Features**:\n34:   - Executes `make gen-check`\n35:   - Verifies no git diff after regeneration\n36:   - Go version 1.24.4\n37:   - Caching enabled\n38:   - Concurrency control enabled\n39:   - Timeout: 15 minutes\n40: \n41: ### 4. Test Coverage Workflow (coverage.yml)\n42: - **Purpose**: Race-enabled coverage tests\n43: - **Triggers**: Pull requests and merge groups\n44: - **Key Features**:\n45:   - Runs `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n46:   - Uploads `coverage.out` as artifact (30-day retention)\n47:   - Integrates with Codecov for coverage reporting\n48:   - Free disk space cleanup for large test runs\n49:   - Go version 1.24\n50:   - Concurrency control enabled\n51:   - Timeout: 30 minutes\n52: \n53: ### 5. E2E Workflow (e2e.yml)\n54: - **Purpose**: End-to-end testing on Kind cluster\n55: - **Triggers**: Pull requests to `main` or `release-*` branches\n56: - **Key Features**:\n57:   - Installs Kind v0.30.0 with `install_only: true`\n58:   - Executes `make e2e` in Kind cluster\n59:   - Captures logs on failure as artifacts\n60:   - Always runs cleanup with `make e2e-clean`\n61:   - Go version 1.23\n62:   - Environment variable `ARTIFACTS_PATH` for log collection\n63:   - Concurrency control enabled\n64:   - Timeout: 60 minutes\n65: \n66: ### 6. Python SDK Tests Workflow (python-sdk-tests.yml)\n67: - **Purpose**: Python SDK unit tests\n68: - **Triggers**: Pull requests and merge groups\n69: - **Key Features**:\n70:   - Python version 3.12\n71:   - Working directory: `python-sdk/`\n72:   - Installs pytest and SDK in editable mode\n73:   - Runs `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n74:   - Pip caching enabled\n75:   - Concurrency control enabled\n76:   - Timeout: 20 minutes\n77: \n78: ### 7. Python Lint Workflow (python-lint.yml)\n79: - **Purpose**: Python code linting with Ruff\n80: - **Triggers**: Pull requests with Python-related file changes\n81: - **Path Filters**: `cmd/cli/**`, `python-sdk/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml`\n82: - **Key Features**:\n83:   - Python version 3.10\n84:   - Uses Ruff with project configuration (`--config pyproject.toml`)\n85:   - Lints entire repository from root\n86:   - Pip caching enabled\n87:   - Concurrency control enabled\n88:   - Timeout: 15 minutes\n89: \n90: ### 8. Spelling Check Workflow (spelling.yml)\n91: - **Purpose**: Spelling verification with codespell\n92: - **Triggers**: Pull requests to `main` or `release-*` branches\n93: - **Key Features**:\n94:   - Python version 3.10\n95:   - Backs up files causing false positives (pyproject.toml, package-lock.json, package.json)\n96:   - Runs codespell with `--check-filenames`\n97:   - Skips specified globs (`.svg`, `.png`, `.git`, etc.)\n98:   - Ignores word list: `fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn`\n99:   - Restores backed-up files after check\n100:   - Concurrency control enabled\n101:   - Timeout: 10 minutes\n102: \n103: ### 9. Copyright Check Workflow (copyright.yml)\n104: - **Purpose**: Copyright header verification\n105: - **Triggers**: Pull requests and merge groups\n106: - **Key Features**:\n107:   - Installs `moreutils` for `sponge` command\n108:   - Executes `make gen-copyright`\n109:   - Verifies no git diff with `git diff --exit-code`\n110:   - Concurrency control enabled\n111:   - Timeout: 15 minutes\n112: \n113: ### 10. Release Workflow (release.yml)\n114: - **Purpose**: Multi-architecture image publishing to GHCR\n115: - **Triggers**: Push to `main` branch or semantic version tags (`v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*`)\n116: - **Key Features**:\n117:   - Uses Docker Buildx for multi-arch builds (amd64, arm64)\n118:   - Logs in to GitHub Container Registry (ghcr.io)\n119:   - Uses semantic version as tag or `latest` for main branch\n120:   - Builds and pushes three images:\n121:     - `workloadmanager` via `make docker-buildx-push`\n122:     - `router` via `make docker-buildx-push-router`\n123:     - `picod` via `make docker-buildx-push-picod`\n124:   - Go version 1.24.4\n125:   - Timeout: 60 minutes\n126:   - Permissions: `contents: write`\n127: \n128: ### 11. Workflow Approval Workflow (approve.yml)\n129: - **Purpose**: Automatic approval for repeat contributors or ok-to-test label\n130: - **Triggers**: `pull_request_target` events (labeled, synchronize)\n131: - **Target Branches**: `main` or `release-*`\n132: - **Key Features**:\n133:   - Uses `pull_request_target` for security\n134:   - Lists workflow runs for head SHA with `action_required` status\n135:   - Approves each workflow run via GitHub API\n136:   - Permissions: `actions: write`, `pull-requests: read`\n137:   - Timeout: 10 minutes\n138: \n139: ### 12. Dependency Update Workflow (dependencies.yml)\n140: - **Purpose**: Periodic Go and Python dependency updates\n141: - **Triggers**: Scheduled (Monday 00:00 UTC) and manual `workflow_dispatch`\n142: - **Key Features**:\n143:   - Updates Go dependencies: `go get -u ./...` and `go mod tidy`\n144:   - Updates Python dependencies: `pip install --upgrade -r requirements.txt`\n145:   - Runs tests to verify compatibility\n146:   - Creates pull request if changes exist\n147:   - Labels PR with `dependencies`\n148:   - Go version 1.24\n149:   - Python version 3.10\n150:   - Caching enabled\n151:   - Concurrency control enabled\n152:   - Timeout: 30 minutes\n153:   - Permissions: `contents: write`, `pull-requests: write`\n154: \n155: ## Implementation Details\n156: \n157: ### Concurrency Control\n158: - Applied to all PR-triggered workflows\n159: - Pattern: `${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.ref }}`\n160: - Cancels in-progress runs when new commits are pushed\n161: - Prevents resource waste and ensures latest code is tested\n162: \n163: ### Caching Strategy\n164: - **Go Modules**: `~/go/pkg/mod` with key `${{ runner.os }}-go-${{ hashFiles('**/go.sum') }}`\n165: - **Python Packages**: `~/.cache/pip` with key `${{ runner.os }}-pip-${{ hashFiles('**/requirements.txt') }}`\n166: - Significantly speeds up workflow execution\n167: \n168: ### Permissions\n169: - **Read-only**: Most workflows use `contents: read`\n170: - **Write access**: Release workflow uses `contents: write` for GHCR\n171: - **Actions write**: Approve workflow uses `actions: write` for workflow approval\n172: - **PR write**: Dependencies workflow uses `pull-requests: write` for PR creation\n173: \n174: ### Security Measures\n175: - Uses `pull_request_target` for workflow approval to prevent malicious PR abuse\n176: - Pinned action versions (e.g., `@v4`, `@v7`)\n177: - Minimal required permissions\n178: - Secrets stored in GitHub Secrets, never hardcoded\n179: \n180: ### Timeout Configuration\n181: - CI: 30 minutes\n182: - Lint: 15 minutes\n183: - Codegen Check: 15 minutes\n184: - Coverage: 30 minutes\n185: - E2E: 60 minutes (accounts for cluster setup and test execution)\n186: - Python SDK Tests: 20 minutes\n187: - Python Lint: 15 minutes\n188: - Spelling: 10 minutes\n189: - Copyright: 15 minutes\n190: - Release: 60 minutes (multi-arch builds)\n191: - Approve: 10 minutes\n192: - Dependencies: 30 minutes\n193: \n194: ### Artifact Management\n195: - **Coverage Report**: Uploaded with 30-day retention\n196: - **E2E Logs**: Uploaded on failure with 7-day retention\n197: - Descriptive artifact names\n198: - Available for download from workflow run page\n199: \n200: ## Testing\n201: \n202: ### Unit Tests\n203: Created comprehensive unit tests in `tests/github/test_workflows.py`:\n204: \n205: - ✅ YAML syntax validation\n206: - ✅ Required field verification\n207: - ✅ Trigger configuration validation\n208: - ✅ Path filtering validation\n209: - ✅ Job step verification\n210: - ✅ Concurrency control verification\n211: - ✅ Timeout configuration verification\n212: - ✅ Runner configuration verification\n213: - ✅ Permissions configuration verification\n214: - ✅ Pinned action versions verification\n215: - ✅ Workflow name verification\n216: \n217: **Test Results**: 29/29 tests passing\n218: \n219: ### Workflow Coverage\n220: All 12 workflows have been implemented with:\n221: - Correct trigger configurations\n222: - Appropriate path filtering\n223: - Proper job steps and dependencies\n224: - Security best practices\n225: - Caching and concurrency\n226: - Comprehensive error handling\n227: \n228: ## Acceptance Criteria Met\n229: \n230: ✅ **1. CI workflow builds Docker image on PR to main/release-* branches**\n231: - Docker Buildx setup and verification\n232: - `make docker-build` execution\n233: \n234: ✅ **2. Lint workflow runs golangci-lint with Go path filtering**\n235: - Path filters for `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`\n236: - `make lint` execution\n237: \n238: ✅ **3. Codegen check workflow verifies no drift on API/Makefile changes**\n239: - `make gen-check` execution\n240: - Git diff verification\n241: \n242: ✅ **4. Test coverage workflow runs race-enabled tests with coverage report**\n243: - `-race` flag enabled\n244: - Coverage artifact upload\n245: - Codecov integration\n246: \n247: ✅ **5. E2E workflow runs tests in Kind with log capture on failure**\n248: - Kind v0.30.0 installation\n249: - Log capture on failure\n250: - Always-run cleanup\n251: \n252: ✅ **6. Python SDK tests run pytest on python-sdk changes**\n253: - Python 3.12 setup\n254: - `python -m pytest tests/ -v` execution\n255: \n256: ✅ **7. Python lint runs Ruff with Python path filtering**\n257: - Path filters for Python files\n258: - Ruff with `--config pyproject.toml`\n259: \n260: ✅ **8. Spelling check runs codespell with file exclusions**\n261: - File backup and restore\n262: - Exclusions and ignore list\n263: \n264: ✅ **9. Copyright check verifies headers with path filtering**\n265: - `make gen-copyright` execution\n266: - Git diff verification\n267: \n268: ✅ **10. Release workflow builds and pushes multi-architecture images to GHCR**\n269: - Multi-arch builds (amd64, arm64)\n270: - GHCR authentication and push\n271: - Semantic version and latest tags\n272: \n273: ✅ **11. Workflow approval approves runs for repeat contributors or ok-to-test label**\n274: - `pull_request_target` usage\n275: - GitHub API approval calls\n276: \n277: ✅ **12. Dependency update workflow periodically updates Go and Python dependencies**\n278: - Scheduled execution (Monday 00:00 UTC)\n279: - Manual trigger via `workflow_dispatch`\n280: - PR creation with changes\n281: \n282: ✅ **13. Workflow concurrency cancels in-progress runs appropriately**\n283: - Concurrency groups configured\n284: - Cancel-in-progress enabled\n285: \n286: ✅ **14. Workflow caching speeds up Go modules, Python packages, and Docker layers**\n287: - Go modules caching\n288: - Python packages caching\n289: - Cache keys based on dependency hashes\n290: \n291: ✅ **15. Workflow artifacts manage logs and reports appropriately**\n292: - Coverage report artifact (30 days)\n293: - E2E logs artifact on failure (7 days)\n294: \n295: ✅ **16. Workflow status reporting provides clear PR check feedback**\n296: - All workflows report status\n297: - Passing/failing status in PR checks\n298: \n299: ✅ **17. Workflow permissions use appropriate security measures**\n300: - Minimal required permissions\n301: - Read permissions for most workflows\n302: - Write permissions only when necessary\n303: \n304: ✅ **18. Workflow timeouts prevent indefinite runs**\n305: - All jobs have timeout configured\n306: - Appropriate timeouts for each job type\n307: \n308: ## File Structure\n309: \n310: ```\n311: .github/\n312: └── workflows/\n313:     ├── ci.yml                      # Docker build verification\n314:     ├── lint.yml                    # Go linting with path filtering\n315:     ├── codegen-check.yml           # Code generation drift detection\n316:     ├── coverage.yml                # Race-enabled coverage tests\n317:     ├── e2e.yml                     # E2E tests on Kind\n318:     ├── python-sdk-tests.yml        # Python SDK unit tests\n319:     ├── python-lint.yml             # Python linting with Ruff\n320:     ├── spelling.yml                # Spelling check with codespell\n321:     ├── copyright.yml               # Copyright header verification\n322:     ├── release.yml                 # Multi-arch image publishing\n323:     ├── approve.yml                 # Workflow approval\n324:     └── dependencies.yml            # Dependency updates\n325: \n326: tests/\n327: └── github/\n328:     └── test_workflows.py          # Comprehensive workflow tests\n329: ```\n330: \n331: ## Next Steps\n332: \n333: 1. **Commit and Push**: Commit all workflow files to the repository\n334: 2. **GitHub Setup**: Ensure repository has required secrets and settings\n335: 3. **Enable Workflows**: Verify workflows are enabled in repository settings\n336: 4. **First PR**: Create a test PR to verify workflow triggers and execution\n337: 5. **Monitor**: Watch initial workflow runs and adjust as needed\n338: 6. **Documentation**: Update project documentation with CI/CD information\n339: \n340: ## Dependencies\n341: \n342: - GitHub Actions (Latest)\n343: - Go 1.24+ (most workflows), Go 1.24.4 (codegen), Go 1.23 (E2E)\n344: - Python 3.10+ (Python lint), Python 3.12 (Python SDK tests)\n345: - Docker 20.10+ with Buildx\n346: - Kind v0.30.0\n347: - golangci-lint 1.50+\n348: - Ruff 0.1+\n349: - pytest 7.0+\n350: - codespell 2.2+\n351: - moreutils (sponge command)\n352: \n353: ## References\n354: \n355: - Delta Specification: `changes/AR-034/delta-spec.md`\n356: - Base Design: `ci-cd/design.md`\n357: - Base Specification: `ci-cd/spec.md`\n358: - AR-033: Makefile 构建目标体系\n359: - AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建\n360: - GitHub Actions Documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/actions\n361: - Docker Buildx Documentation: https://docs.docker.com/buildx/working-with-buildx/\n362: - Kind Documentation: https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/\n\n(End of file - total 362 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034 Implementation Summary\n\n## Overview\n\nImplemented 12 comprehensive GitHub Actions workflows for CI/CD automation in the AgentCube project, covering build verification, linting, testing, code quality checks, end-to-end testing, Python SDK validation, container image publishing, dependency updates, and workflow approval mechanisms.\n\n## Workflows Implemented\n\n### 1. CI Workflow (ci.yml)\n- **Purpose**: Docker build verification on pull requests\n- **Triggers**: Pull requests to `main` or `release-*` branches\n- **Key Features**:\n  - Uses Docker Buildx for multi-architecture builds\n  - Verifies `docker` and `buildx` versions\n  - Executes `make docker-build`\n  - Timeout: 30 minutes\n  - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n\n### 2. Lint Workflow (lint.yml)\n- **Purpose**: Go code linting with path filtering","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md","time":{"start":1775886486545,"end":1775886486564}}}}
