{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886493338,"sessionID":"ses_284eae57bffeVf5e1aq0wThMJ0","part":{"id":"prt_d7b15666c0015bJ0FijXdauSgl","messageID":"msg_d7b154c54001ZXPv19WnjgRxs1","sessionID":"ses_284eae57bffeVf5e1aq0wThMJ0","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-559bcf2082bd44bdb4616e84ce509b16","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-034/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module**: `.github`\n4: **Language**: `YAML`\n5: **Size**: `L`\n6: **Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n7: \n8: ## Task Breakdown\n9: \n10: ### Task 1: Create .github directory structure\n11: - [ ] Create .github/workflows/ directory if it doesn't exist\n12: - [ ] Create .github/actions/ directory for reusable actions\n13: - [ ] Create .github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/ directory for issue templates\n14: - [ ] Create .github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/ directory for PR templates\n15: - [ ] Verify directory permissions are correct\n16: - [ ] Add .github/ to .gitignore if not already present\n17: - [ ] Document directory structure in README.md\n18: \n19: **Verification**:\n20: ```bash\n21: test -d .github/workflows && echo \"workflows exists\" || echo \"workflows missing\"\n22: test -d .github/actions && echo \"actions exists\" || echo \"actions missing\"\n23: ls -la .github/\n24: ```\n25: \n26: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n27: - All required directories are created\n28: - Directory structure follows GitHub best practices\n29: - Documentation is updated\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ### Task 2: Create ci-pr-checks workflow\n34: - [ ] Create .github/workflows/ci-pr-checks.yml\n35: - [ ] Set workflow trigger on pull_request to main branch\n36: - [ ] Set workflow trigger on push to main branch\n37: - [ ] Add job matrix for Go and Python checks\n38: - [ ] Configure checkout action with fetch-depth: 0\n39: - [ ] Set up Go environment (version 1.21+)\n40: - [ ] Set up Python environment (version 3.11+)\n41: - [ ] Add job to run Go tests (make test-go)\n42: - [ ] Add job to run Python tests (make test-python)\n43: - [ ] Add job to run Go linting (make lint-go)\n44: - [ ] Add job to run Python linting (make lint-python)\n45: - [ ] Add job to check code formatting (make format-check)\n46: - [ ] Configure job dependencies (lint before tests)\n47: - [ ] Add artifact upload for test results\n48: - [ ] Add coverage report upload to Codecov\n49: - [ ] Configure job timeout (30 minutes)\n50: - [ ] Add job status checks required for PR merge\n51: \n52: **Verification**:\n53: ```bash\n54: test -f .github/workflows/ci-pr-checks.yml && echo \"workflow exists\" || echo \"workflow missing\"\n55: yamllint .github/workflows/ci-pr-checks.yml || echo \"YAML syntax valid\"\n56: grep -q \"on: pull_request\" .github/workflows/ci-pr-checks.yml && echo \"PR trigger configured\" || echo \"PR trigger missing\"\n57: ```\n58: \n59: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n60: - Workflow file is syntactically valid YAML\n61: - Workflow triggers on PR and push to main\n62: - All check jobs are defined\n63: - Jobs have proper dependencies and timeouts\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ### Task 3: Create lint-checks workflow\n68: - [ ] Create .github/workflows/lint-checks.yml\n69: - [ ] Set workflow trigger on pull_request to all branches\n70: - [ ] Set workflow trigger on push to all branches\n71: - [ ] Add job for Go linting\n72: - [ ] Configure golangci-lint with .golangci.yml config\n73: - [ ] Add job for Python linting with ruff\n74: - [ ] Add job for Python type checking with mypy\n75: - [ ] Add job for YAML linting with yamllint\n76: - [ ] Add job for markdown linting with markdownlint\n77: - [ ] Add job for shell script linting with shellcheck\n78: - [ ] Configure caching for linter installations\n79: - [ ] Add job failure annotations\n80: - [ ] Configure job to run on ubuntu-latest\n81: - [ ] Set job timeout (15 minutes)\n82: \n83: **Verification**:\n84: ```bash\n85: test -f .github/workflows/lint-checks.yml && echo \"workflow exists\" || echo \"workflow missing\"\n86: grep -q \"golangci-lint\" .github/workflows/lint-checks.yml && echo \"Go linting configured\" || echo \"Go linting missing\"\n87: grep -q \"ruff\" .github/workflows/lint-checks.yml && echo \"Python linting configured\" || echo \"Python linting missing\"\n88: ```\n89: \n90: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n91: - All linting jobs are defined\n92: - Jobs run on appropriate events\n93: - Caching is configured\n94: - Failure annotations are enabled\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: ### Task 4: Create unit-tests workflow\n99: - [ ] Create .github/workflows/unit-tests.yml\n100: - [ ] Set workflow trigger on pull_request and push\n101: - [ ] Add job matrix for Go tests (multiple Go versions)\n102: - [ ] Add job matrix for Python tests (multiple Python versions)\n103: - [ ] Configure Go test job with race detection\n104: - [ ] Configure Python test job with pytest\n105: - [ ] Add test coverage collection for Go\n106: - [ ] Add test coverage collection for Python\n107: - [ ] Upload coverage reports as artifacts\n108: - [ ] Upload coverage to Codecov\n109: - [ ] Add test result parsing for JUnit XML\n110: - [ ] Configure test timeout (20 minutes)\n111: - [ ] Add test retries on failure (max 2)\n112: - [ ] Add test summary to PR comments\n113: \n114: **Verification**:\n115: ```bash\n116: test -f .github/workflows/unit-tests.yml && echo \"workflow exists\" || echo \"workflow missing\"\n117: grep -q \"race\" .github/workflows/unit-tests.yml && echo \"Race detection configured\" || echo \"Race detection missing\"\n118: grep -q \"codecov\" .github/workflows/unit-tests.yml && echo \"Codecov configured\" || echo \"Codecov missing\"\n119: ```\n120: \n121: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n122: - Unit tests run for all supported versions\n123: - Coverage is collected and uploaded\n124: - Test results are parsed and displayed\n125: - Race detection is enabled\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ### Task 5: Create integration-tests workflow\n130: - [ ] Create .github/workflows/integration-tests.yml\n131: - [ ] Set workflow trigger on pull_request and push to main\n132: - [ ] Set workflow trigger on nightly schedule (cron: 0 2 * * *)\n133: - [ ] Add job for Go integration tests\n134: - [ ] Add job for Python integration tests\n135: - [ ] Add job for end-to-end tests\n136: - [ ] Set up required services (Docker compose)\n137: - [ ] Configure test environment with secrets\n138: - [ ] Add database setup and teardown\n139: - [ ] Configure test data fixtures\n140: - [ ] Add test isolation between tests\n141: - [ ] Configure test timeout (45 minutes)\n142: - [ ] Upload test logs as artifacts\n143: - [ ] Add test result summarization\n144: - [ ] Configure test failure notifications\n145: \n146: **Verification**:\n147: ```bash\n148: test -f .github/workflows/integration-tests.yml && echo \"workflow exists\" || echo \"workflow missing\"\n149: grep -q \"cron:\" .github/workflows/integration-tests.yml && echo \"Schedule configured\" || echo \"Schedule missing\"\n150: grep -q \"docker-compose\" .github/workflows/integration-tests.yml && echo \"Services configured\" || echo \"Services missing\"\n151: ```\n152: \n153: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n154: - Integration tests run on schedule and events\n155: - Services are properly set up and torn down\n156: - Tests are isolated and repeatable\n157: - Logs are collected on failure\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ### Task 6: Create build-docker workflow\n162: - [ ] Create .github/workflows/build-docker.yml\n163: - [ ] Set workflow trigger on pull_request and push to main\n164: - [ ] Set workflow trigger on release (types: [published])\n165: - [ ] Add job matrix for multiple platforms (linux/amd64, linux/arm64)\n166: - [ ] Configure Docker Buildx for multi-platform builds\n167: - [ ]