ches/main/protection\n680: ```\n681: \n682: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n683: - Branch protection is configured\n684: - Required workflows are enforced\n685: - Review requirements are set\n686: - Security settings are enabled\n687: \n688: ---\n689: \n690: ### Task 24: Add workflow security hardening\n691: - [ ] Review all workflows for security best practices\n692: - [ ] Use pinned action versions (not @latest)\n693: - [ ] Use minimal permissions for workflows\n694: - [ ] Configure token permissions (read-only where possible)\n695: - [ ] Add workflow input validation\n696: - [ ] Add secret scanning patterns\n697: - [ ] Configure artifact retention policies\n698: - [ ] Add audit logging\n699: - [ ] Document security considerations\n700: \n701: **Verification**:\n702: ```bash\n703: grep -q \"@v\" .github/workflows/ci-pr-checks.yml && echo \"Pinned versions used\" || echo \"Unpinned versions found\"\n704: grep -q \"permissions:\" .github/workflows/ci-pr-checks.yml && echo \"Permissions configured\" || echo \"Permissions not configured\"\n705: ```\n706: \n707: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n708: - All actions use pinned versions\n709: - Minimal permissions are configured\n710: - Security best practices are followed\n711: - Audit logging is enabled\n712: \n713: ---\n714: \n715: ### Task 25: Create workflow maintenance guide\n716: - [ ] Create workflow maintenance checklist\n717: - [ ] Document workflow update process\n718: - [ ] Document secret rotation process\n719: - [ ] Document workflow troubleshooting steps\n720: - [ ] Document performance tuning guidelines\n721: - [ ] Document backup and recovery procedures\n722: - [ ] Create workflow monitoring dashboard\n723: - [ ] Configure alerts for workflow failures\n724: - [ ] Document escalation procedures\n725: - [ ] Schedule regular workflow reviews\n726: \n727: **Verification**:\n728: ```bash\n729: test -f docs/workflow-maintenance.md && echo \"Maintenance guide exists\" || echo \"Maintenance guide missing\"\n730: grep -q \"troubleshooting\" docs/workflow-maintenance.md && echo \"Troubleshooting documented\" || echo \"Troubleshooting not documented\"\n731: ```\n732: \n733: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n734: - Maintenance guide is comprehensive\n735: - All procedures are documented\n736: - Monitoring is configured\n737: - Escalation procedures are defined\n738: \n739: ---\n740: \n741: ### Task 26: Final validation and cleanup\n742: - [ ] Review all workflows for consistency\n743: - [ ] Ensure all workflows follow naming conventions\n744: - [ ] Verify all workflow comments are accurate\n745: - [ ] Remove any debug or test code\n746: - [ ] Verify all environment variables are documented\n747: - [ ] Verify all secrets are documented\n748: - [ ] Test all workflows one final time\n749: - [ ] Verify documentation is complete\n750: - [ ] Verify badges are working\n751: - [ ] Clean up temporary files\n752: - [ ] Final code review of all workflow files\n753: - [ ] Update CHANGE.md with implementation details\n754: \n755: **Verification**:\n756: ```bash\n757: yamllint .github/workflows/*.yml\n758: find .github -name \"*.tmp\" -o -name \"*.bak\" | wc -l\n759: grep -r \"TODO\\|FIXME\" .github/workflows/\n760: ```\n761: \n762: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n763: - All workflows are consistent and well-documented\n764: - No temporary or debug code remains\n765: - All workflows pass final tests\n766: - Documentation is complete\n767: - CHANGE.md is updated\n768: \n769: ---\n770: \n771: ## Summary\n772: \n773: **Total Tasks**: 26\n774: **Estimated Effort**: L (Large) - 40-60 hours\n775: \n776: ### Key Deliverables\n777: 1. **12 GitHub Actions workflows**:\n778:    - ci-pr-checks.yml - PR validation and checks\n779:    - lint-checks.yml - Code linting across all languages\n780:    - unit-tests.yml - Unit testing with coverage\n781:    - integration-tests.yml - Integration and E2E testing\n782:    - build-docker.yml - Multi-platform Docker builds\n783:    - security-scan.yml - Security vulnerability scanning\n784:    - release.yml - Automated release process\n785:    - deploy-staging.yml - Staging deployment\n786:    - deploy-production.yml - Production deployment\n787:    - docs-build.yml - Documentation build and deployment\n788:    - dependency-update.yml - Automated dependency updates\n789:    - notify-slack.yml - Slack notifications (integrated into workflows)\n790: 2. **5 reusable actions** in .github/actions/\n791: 3. **Configuration files** (Dependabot, CODEOWNERS, templates)\n792: 4. **Documentation** (GitHub Actions guide, maintenance guide)\n793: 5. **Security hardening** and branch protection\n794: 6. **Monitoring and notifications**\n795: \n796: ### Success Criteria\n797: - All 12 workflows are implemented and tested\n798: - Workflows follow GitHub Actions best practices\n799: - All security scans pass (or findings are documented)\n800: - Workflows integrate with existing Makefile build system\n801: - Documentation is comprehensive and accurate\n802: - Branch protection is configured\n803: - Monitoring and notifications are working\n804: - All workflows can be tested locally with act\n805: \n806: ### Dependencies\n807: - AR-033: Makefile build system (workflows depend on Makefile targets)\n808: - AR-032: Dockerfile multi-stage builds (build workflow depends on Dockerfiles)\n809: - GitHub repository with Actions enabled\n810: - Required GitHub secrets (DockerHub, PyPI, Slack, etc.)\n811: - Go 1.21+ toolchain\n812: - Python 3.11+ with pip\n813: - Docker 20.10+\n814: \n815: ### Blocked By\n816: - None (design stage ST-3 completed)\n817: \n818: ### Blocks\n819: - AR-035: Deployment Automation (depends on CI/CD workflows)\n820: - AR-036: Monitoring and Observability (depends on CI/CD workflows)\n821: \n822: ### Notes\n823: - All workflows should use pinned action versions (not @latest)\n824: - Workflows should follow the principle of least privilege\n825: - Caching should be configured for all expensive operations\n826: - All workflows should have appropriate timeouts\n